The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, June 26, 2004 				 One-stop shop for Bharti services
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, June 25: Bharti Tele-Ventures today merged the key corporate account functions of its mobility and fixed-line businesses with the broadband and data group of Bharti Infotel Ltd, creating a new strategic business unit (SBU) to be named Enterprise Business.																								The company announced the major initiative as part of its target to emerge as the leader in the key corporate account segment. Firms that had to deal separately with AirTel for mobile services, Touchtel for fixed-line services and Infotel for broadband can now get all three services through Enterprise Business.																								As part of the plan to grab major corporate accounts with the offer of enhanced services, Bharti plans to synergise and make all its products and services available through a single window.																								Sunil Bharti Mittal, chairman and group managing director of Bharti Enterprises, said, This initiative is designed to ensure that synergetic businesses are run along similar lines tapping the best resources available across our businesses through a single point contact.																								Currently, the data and broadband group, Bharti Infotel Ltd, provides data solutions and broadband services to companies, while the mobility and fixed-line businesses cater to the wireless and fixed-line service requirements of large companies.																								The SBU will be a part of Bharti Infotel Limited and will be headed by Jai Menon as its joint president. He will also continue to spearhead the groups information technology (IT) and technology functions as corporate director - IT and technology.																								As a result of this restructuring, Menon will report to Badri Agarwal, president, Bharti Infotel Limited, for the Enterprise Business, while he would continue to report to the group chairman and managing director for the IT and technology functions.																								Rajiv Sharma, chief of the broadband and data group, Bharti Infotel, will become CEO - Enterprise Business. 
